doc_prompt = (
    "Please convert the following technical troubleshooting content into valid **Confluence Storage Format (XHTML/XML)** "
    "that can be directly used with the REST API (with `representation: storage`).\n\n"
    "**Strict formatting rules:**\n"
    "1. Use valid XHTML syntax only — all tags must be closed properly.\n"
    "2. Headings:\n"
    "   - Use <h2> for main sections\n"
    "   - Use <h3> for sub-sections\n"
    "3. Bullet lists:\n"
    "   - Use <ul> and <li> tags\n"
    "4. Bold text:\n"
    "   - Use <strong>...</strong>\n"
    "5. Inline code:\n"
    "   - Use <code>...</code>\n"
    "6. Code blocks:\n"
    "   - Use the Confluence code macro in this exact format:\n"
    "     <ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\">\n"
    "       <ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">bash</ac:parameter>\n"
    "       <ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[\n"
    "       # your code here\n"
    "       ]]></ac:plain-text-body>\n"
    "     </ac:structured-macro>\n"
    "7. Links:\n"
    "   - Use <a href=\"https://...\">link text</a>\n"
    "8. Do **not** add any extra commentary, explanations, or markdown formatting.\n"
    "9. Return **only** the XHTML content block — no headers, no YAML, no markdown, no markdown code fences.\n\n"
    "Here is the content to be converted:\n"
    "---\n"
    f"{doc_input}\n"
    "---"
)
